votebox.middle.ballot

Class WriteInCardElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • votebox.middle.ballot.SelectableCardElement
      • votebox.middle.ballot.WriteInCardElement

  • public final class WriteInCardElement
extends SelectableCardElement
    A WriteInCardElement is a SelectableCardElement whose candidate name can be modified. This class extends SelectableCardElement, because the WriteInCardElement is a special kind of selectable ballot element -- one that can start a prompt and have its corresponding image be rewritten. Author: Mircea C. Berechet Added to project: 08/06/2013

    • Method Detail

      • select

        public boolean select()
               throws CardStrategyException
        The outside calls this method if they wish to attempt to select this card element. It overrides the SelectableCardElement's select method. In addition to attempting to select this card element, the WriteInCardElement's select method starts a GUI that prompts a voter to type in his preferred candidate's name.
        Overrides:
        select in class SelectableCardElement
        Throws:
        CardStrategyException - This method throws if the strategy runs into a problem.

      • startWriteInCandidateGUI

        public void startWriteInCandidateGUI()
        This method starts a WriteInCandidateGUI that prompts a voter to type in the name of his preferred Write-In Candidate. It reads the type of write-in from this CardElement's properties and opens an appropriate GUI (regular or presidential).
